Rustenburg High choir sings Freddie Mercury's hit, Bohemian Rhapsody. JOHANNESBURG - The Rustenburg High School choir has become an internet sensation with their rendition of Freddie Mercury's hit, Bohemian Rhapsody. In the video, the choir pays tribute to the greatest performer of all time. The video has gone viral, just in hours after the school shared it on their Facebook page. READ: 'Bohemian Rhapsody' rocks with $50m, 'Nutcracker' crumbles Bohemian Rhapsody has been made to a music biopic. It premiered in London in October 2018, reflecting the enduring appeal of Queen and their legendary frontman 27 years on from his death. The Queen lead singer, Freddie Mercury died in November 1991. Watch the video above